oai_dc:dc.dc:title: DESIGN AND PERFORMANCE OF SEA WALLS IN MISSISSIPPI SOUND
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Escoffier, Francis F.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: seawall design
Mississippi Sound
hurricane impacts
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The purpose of this paper is to describe briefly the various types of sea walls that have been constructed on Mississippi Sound, the performance of each type, and the conclusions with regard to sea wall design that can be drawn from this information.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 2 (1951): Proceedings of Second Conference on Coastal Engineering, Houston, Texas, 1951.; 23
